    "body": "@richard-ramos \r\n\r\n> if using a local build, the DEBUG flag is always active, and switching it makes no difference\r\n\r\nFor local build we always set log level to `DEBUG`. Indeed, the switch won't affect anything.\r\nHere's the code that checks `isDebugEnabled` switch on startup:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/a2aedb5c6a699c154382f75d9c5a7e6e641fa14c/src/app/boot/app_controller.nim#L451-L454\r\n\r\nWe could add `else: setLogLevel(chronicles.LogLevel.INFO)`, but using always using `DEBUG` for local build makes sense to me. Maybe we should change the behaviour of the switch in this case? Maybe even hide it?\r\n\r\n> The same happens in release version, except that the log level is always INFO and it's not possible to switch the DEBUG flag\r\n\r\nFor me it's the opposite (but also wrong) ðŸ˜„ \r\nI run `make RELEASE=true -j10 run`. I still get debug output and `DEBUG` switch is always on!\r\n\r\n<img width=\"591\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/25482501/1a536251-b1a2-433f-93c7-40ddcd9b7072\">\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nI think we should reconsider the behaviour of this switch. Requirements would be nice ðŸ™‚ I'd be glad to give input.\r\n\r\nâš ï¸  But I don't think this is of any urgency. This switch is only used by devs and the behaviour can be controlled by env variables or CLI flags.\r\n\r\ncc @John-44 @iurimatias ",
