    "body": "With regards to above conversation, currently testing in non-release, the the mode is always Debug. Below explains that the bug is not in status-go, but in the config/setup on the nim side.\r\n\r\nDiscovered that the bug is happening at start up where the last value set is overwritten for some reason by a DEBUG value, and itâ€™s always set to DEBUG for logLevel. This result in the button always being set to Debug. So I am currently investigating why the value is always DEBUG at start up. Why can't we fetch the value in database and use that as start up value.\r\n\r\nThis DEBUG value comes from this code which always set the default value to DEBUG depending on the type of build currently used :\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/2abfe0fa0cab36e7f850fbae4deb1965351380b8/src/env_cli_vars.nim#L10\r\n\r\nThe setting of the default log can be observed in this sequence, (I just added a few logs to observe what's happening) and we can see the DEBUG being set : \r\n\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nBG 2024-01-25 10:59:30.407-08:00 Account logged in                         \r\n topics=\"accounts-service\" tid=1272478 file=service.nim:694\r\n3 ---> GetNodeConfigFromDB\r\n4 ---> loadNodeConfig  INFO\r\n...\r\n---> inserting in node_config LogLevel:  DEBUG\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actions \r\n\r\nBased on above anylsis, I believe there's no need to force the default value for the logs at boot from the config perspective.\r\n\r\nHere is the result : \r\n\r\n[Screencast from 2024-01-25 02:06:00 PM.webm](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/2589171/ca6f22c8-3502-49a9-9a5b-f03368781d74)\r\n",
